Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?
A.
A programming language is a formal language, which comprises a set of instructions used to produce various
kinds of output. Programming languages are used in computer programming to create programs that implement
specific algorithms

What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A.The Java Development Kit (JDK) is a software development environment used for developing Java applications
and applets. It includes the Java Runtime Environment (JRE), an interpreter/loader (Java), a compiler (javac),
an archiver (jar), a documentation generator (Javadoc) and other tools needed in Java development.
JRE stands for “Java Runtime Environment” and may also be written as “Java RTE.”
The Java Runtime Environment provides the minimum requirements for executing a Java application;
it consists of the Java Virtual Machine (JVM), core classes, and supporting files.

What is IDE?
A.An integrated development environment (IDE) is a software application that provides comprehensive
facilities to computer programmers for software development, which mean it enable users to write ,
read and compile programming language code.  An IDE normally consists of a source code editor, build
automation tools, and a debugger. Most modern IDEs have intelligent code completion.

What are the IDEs available in the market to support java?
A.IDEs available in the market to support Java are Eclipse, Intellij, Netbeans, BlueJ etc.

Explain the entire java life cycle.

A.First we write a program say sample.java, Then this program in java language is complied using javac compiler and is
converted to machine independent bytecode. The code that is generated after compilation is a.class file. Last step is
execution. The bytecode generated by the compiler will be executed by Java Virtual Machine (JVM). Input to the JVM is
bytecode and output is machine code (0’s and 1’s) which will be executed by the CPU of the local machine.
