What is the entry point of an application?

A. The entry point of an application is a program or method or class that starts the application.
 If you have an application bundled in a JAR file, you need some way to indicate which class within
 the JAR file is your application's entry point.
For Example The main method is the entry point of a Java application.

Why main is static?
A. Main method is static in  Java so virtual Machine can call it without creating any instance of class which
contains main method.

